    "long_instructions": "# Do This:\r\n1. Write a program where the Painter paints lines on the left side of each taxi:\r\n\t- **Hint:** If there is not a taxi to the east of the painter, the painter should move forward, instead of paint (see the image below).\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://images.code.org/ae10359090c90db9ab0d60d5a2da497f-Screenshot 2025-02-03 104336.png\" style=\"width:200px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\r\n\r\n<details style=\"background-color: #e0d1ec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;\">\r\n    <summary style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-weight: bold; color: black;\">Need help with your algorithm?</summary>\r\n    <div style=\"margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;\">\r\n    \t<p style=\"color: black;\">Here is one approach to solving this problem.</p>\r\n        <pre style=\"background-color: #333333; color: white;\">\r\nwhile the Painter has paint\r\n  if the Painter can move east\r\n    move\r\n \r\n  paint with the color\r\n \r\n  if the Painter can move forward\r\n    move\r\n\t  </pre>\r\n    </div>\r\n</details>",
    "start_sources": {
      "files": {
        "0": {
          "id": "0",
          "name": "main.py",
          "language": "py",
          "contents": "from neighborhood import Painter\n\n# Create Painter object\nangie = Painter()\n\n# Function to move while can\ndef move_while_can():\n  while angie.can_move():\n    angie.move()\n\n# Function to take all the paint\ndef take_all_paint():\n  while angie.is_on_bucket():\n    angie.take_paint()\n\n# Function to turn right\ndef turn_right():\n  angie.turn_left()\n  angie.turn_left()\n  angie.turn_left()\n\n# ADD NEW FUNCTION DEFINITION HERE\n\n\n\n# ADD USER-DEFINED FUNCTION AND PAINTER METHOD CALLS HERE\n\n\n\n\n\n\n",
          "folderId": "0",
          "active": true,
          "open": true
        }
      },
      "folders": {
      }
    },
